These are top quality 300 Stainless Steel Pins with Grade 8 Black Oxide Allen Head Screws (Two Allens Included) and already have the Locktite applied. Simply replace existing pins and Snug (do not over tighten) screws for a permanent fix of the stock pins that have a tendency to "WALK" out of place. These pins fix that problem before it starts. title: For Sale/Trade:  Kel-Tec PF9, +Belt Clip, Fluffed and Buffed, BETTER than new
postcontent:
Kel-Tec PF9 with less than 120 rounds through it. 
Brown frame, blued slide. Has belt clip installed (in matching blued finish). 
Gun has been "fluffed and buffed" and operates MUCH better than new. 
Gun looks and feels new, but has many improvements over new. 
Looking for $300.

Selling only to fund purchase of a new gun.  
Also open to trade for a shotgun (12 through 20 gage), or a semi-auto rifle in 5.56 or 7.62 or other readily available caliber.  Let me know what you have. 

Comes with 1 magazine, finger extension mag bottom (installed), flat mag bottom, trigger lock, manual, original hard case, belt clip (installed), original frame pins (if want to remove belt clip). 
Basically everything you get with the new gun, plus the belt clip. 

Also, I filed down the sharp edges on the ridges that are on the back of the grip.
This greatly improved comfort for me when shooting without gloves. Visually no different, simply more comfortable. 

Whats a "fluff and buff"?
You can google it, but basically it is doing all the hand finish work that Kel-Tec does not do to keep prices down. This helps the gun operate smoother, giving better feel and (IMO) better accuracy and less perceived recoil. 
Here is what was done:
Polished feed ramp
Smoothed out machining and casting marks in areas of contact on slide and frame
Broke sharp edge at bottom of bore in frame where barrel rides and polished inside bore
Broke sharp edges where feed ramp meets frame
Polished slide rails
Polished outside of chamber where it slides against slide
Broke sharp edges of magazine where grips casing and polished these edges
**NOTE: Polished means improved surface finish through polishing using a felt bob and various stages of polishing compound. I only went up to a high-gloss in the feed areas and around the chamber, as these areas build up carbon quickly and the higher gloss finish does a better job of resisting build-up.

postcontent:
Selling this because it's an extra.  This is an SDS Warrior helmet in excellent condition, I'm not sure it's ever even been used by it's amazing condition.  It is a size medium and comes with new pads (no worries about someone else's sweaty head having been in it).  The chin strap assembly has been lightly used but is clean and in good condition.  The helmet will come with an ACU Digital Camo cover that is in excellent condition.  These are the same helmets currently being worn by our troops so you can be assured they are tough and extremely well made.

Usually helmets have been bounced around, have flaking paint and look used but this one is beautiful.  It has the single factory drilled front hole for mounting night vision equipment should you want to go full tactical or go hog hunting or for protecting your melon during tornado season.  The number one cause of death during a tornado are head injuries so this helmet is a multi-tasker that can save your life.  I collect helmets but we do use them during tornado season when needed.

In a bind (those of you with family during the holiday know what i mean) so I'm dropping this to $150 which is a great deal if you plan on using it or keeping it as a reminder of a loved one's service.  They don't come around in this condition very often so if you are considering such a thing this is an excellent one.  

FtF OKC Only - cash only please.
